Sentencas: To evaluate the long-term thermal stability of the cathode, they are heated at 800 degrees C for 100 h in the air, and no contaminant is found.

Sentencas: In the optimal amount of Pr and Co (Sr2.7Pr0.3Fe1.8Co0.2O7-8), area-specific resistance (ASR) of 0.058 O.cm2 and maximum output power density of 745 mW/cm2 are obtained at 800 degrees C. Strong oxygen-reducing reaction (ORR) activity and long-term thermal stability make Sr2.7Pr0.3Fe1.8Co0.2O7-8 an appropriate alternative cathode material for IT-SOFC.
